# Testing

Follow [docs/TESTING.md](docs/TESTING.md). Summary for agents:

## Where tests go

- Pure logic → colocated `*.test.ts` next to the module
- React UI → `*.test.tsx` with Testing Library + `renderWithProviders` from `#/test/test-utils`
- Migrations / SECURITY DEFINER / RLS → `tests/db/**/*.test.ts` in the **same PR**
- P0 user journeys only → `e2e/**/*.spec.ts`

## Rules

- Prefer unit tests for new pure helpers over brittle full-page UI tests
- Mock Supabase with `createRpcMock` / `vi.mock('#/shared/api/supabase')` — never hit the **remote** production project from automated tests
- Do not mock away the behavior under test
- When asserting UI copy, match existing Norwegian strings in the component
- Local Supabase (`supabase start` / `db reset`) is **test/CI only**; day-to-day app work stays remote-first
- After changing `normalize_member_phone` or coupon RPCs, update TS phone tests and DB parity/RPC cases
- Skip E2E for minesweeper/solitaire engines if unit tests cover them; a “window opens” smoke is enough if needed

## Commands

- `npm run test` — unit + component
- `npm run test:db` — local Supabase required
- `npm run test:e2e` — Playwright
- `npm run test:coverage` — thresholds on pure modules
